parameters: Umi: "Grandma... Are you not feeling well...?"

Umi's Mother: "What are you talking about? Grandma is always full of
energy, right?"
Umi: "No way! Grandma is always in bed!"

Grandma: "I stay here because I like it. But I'm sorry, Umi... You want to
play outside with Grandma, don't you?"

Umi: "I want to play, but... Umi is okay! I'll go pray for Grandma to get
better quickly!"
Umi's Father: "Hey, Umi. Are you going somewhere?"

Umi: "Yeah. I'm going to pray to the god Kureshiresama for Grandma's
illness to be cured."

Umi's Father: "Kureshirei-sama, huh. Oh, that's very good of you, Umi! If
you pray, I'm sure she'll get better."

Umi: "That's not true... I've been praying all the time, but Grandma isn't
getting any better."

Umi's Father: "Ah, I'm back... Sorry, I searched all over the forest, but I
couldn't find any grapes."

Umi: (Grandma... used to love grapes... Maybe she could get better if she
could eat some...)
